Adjust racks to middle and top positions and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Halve and peel @shallot{1}. Finely chop one half (save other half for another use). Slice @Yukon Gold potatoes{12%ounces} into ¼-inch-thick rounds (no need to peel).

Lightly oil a #baking sheet{}. In a #large bowl{}, combine potatoes, @olive oil{2%tablespoon}, @garlic powder{6%teaspoon}, and a couple large pinches of @salt{} and @pepper{}; toss until potatoes are completely coated. Arrange potatoes on prepared sheet into clusters (about 6 slightly overlapping slices each). Roast on middle rack for ~{10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, toss @green beans{1%ounce} on a second baking sheet with a drizzle of @olive oil{5%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Once potatoes have roasted 10 minutes, remove from oven and sprinkle with @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}. Return to middle rack and place green beans on top rack. Roast until potatoes are tender, cheese is lightly browned, and green beans are tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

While green beans roast, pat @sirloin steak{14%ounces} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{4%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook to desired doneness, ~{4-6%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium heat. Add shallot and cook, stirring, until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Pour in @sherry vinegar{2 1/2%teaspoon} (save the rest for another use). Simmer until reduced by half, ~{15-30%seconds}. Stir in @water{1/4%cup} and @beef stock concentrate{1}. Simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat. Stir in @sour cream{2%tablespoon} and @butter{1%tablespoon}. Season with salt and pepper.

Slice steak against the grain. Divide potato clusters, green beans, and steak between plates. Top steak with sauce and serve.

